[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is the current definition of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete#doc\">docs#ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete</a> (which says that there exists a maximal element with valuation &lt; 1) correct?<br>\nIn particular, the map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>‚àà</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></msub><mo>‚Üí</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>‚à™</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">‚ä•</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">v : R[X_i]_{i \\in \\mathbb{Q}_{&gt;0}} \\to \\mathbb{Q} \\cup\\{\\bot\\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0196em;vertical-align:-0.2697em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0785em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3322em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">‚àà</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathbb mtight\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3173em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.357em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mrel mtight\">&gt;</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1709em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2697em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8556em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">‚à™</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">‚ä•</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>‚Ü¶</mo><mi>deg</mi><mo>‚Å°</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\mapsto \\deg f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚Ü¶</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">de<span style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span> (with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0785em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> having degree <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6595em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span></span></span></span>) is a valuation that satisfies <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete#doc\">docs#ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete</a> (because the only element with degree &lt; 0 is 0) but it doesn't feel like a discrete valuation to me.</p>",
        "id": 542909684,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1759485391
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>feels similar to <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/27990\">#27990</a> <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 542911580,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759485973
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i guess the question to ask here is what do you want to gain from a definition of \"discrete valuation\" specifically in this case where you apply it to not-fields</p>",
        "id": 542911701,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759486020
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Pinging <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"130609\">@Antoine Chambert-Loir</span> with whom we had similar discussions.</p>",
        "id": 542922439,
        "sender_full_name": "Filippo A. E. Nuccio",
        "timestamp": 1759490069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would you rather it be that the value group is not densely ordered?</p>",
        "id": 542927264,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1759491938
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which is stronger, and implies the current definition afaiu</p>",
        "id": 542927398,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1759491987
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The IsDiscrete currently is sufficient for the iff statement that says that a field F with IsDiscrete valuative relation will have an IsDVR valuation subring, again afaiu</p>",
        "id": 542927570,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1759492050
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"439483\">Andrew Yang</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Discrete.20valuation/near/542909684\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is the current definition of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete#doc\">docs#ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete</a> (which says that there exists a maximal element with valuation &lt; 1) correct?<br>\nIn particular, the map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>R</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>‚àà</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mrow><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></msub><mo>‚Üí</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi><mo>‚à™</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">‚ä•</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">v : R[X_i]_{i \\in \\mathbb{Q}_{&gt;0}} \\to \\mathbb{Q} \\cup\\{\\bot\\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0196em;vertical-align:-0.2697em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0785em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">]</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3322em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">‚àà</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathbb mtight\">Q</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3173em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.357em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mrel mtight\">&gt;</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1709em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2697em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚Üí</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8556em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">‚à™</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">‚ä•</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>‚Ü¶</mo><mi>deg</mi><mo>‚Å°</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\mapsto \\deg f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚Ü¶</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\">de<span style=\"margin-right:0.01389em;\">g</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span> (with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3117em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0785em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> having degree <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6595em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span></span></span></span>) is a valuation that satisfies <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete#doc\">docs#ValuativeRel.IsDiscrete</a> (because the only element with degree &lt; 0 is 0) but it doesn't feel like a discrete valuation to me.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If the value group is <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Q}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8556em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span></span></span></span> then it won't be discrete.</p>",
        "id": 542938686,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759495750
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The value group in the sense of <code>ValuativeRel</code> is actually the value <em>group</em>, not the image of the valuation. So even if you have a valuation taking values in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Q}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8556em;vertical-align:-0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Q</span></span></span></span> whose image is the nonnegative rationals, the value group would still be the rationals.</p>",
        "id": 542939202,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759495924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It would be helpful if you could say explicitly what you expect the value group to be in your example, as a type satisfying <code>LinearOrderedCommmGroupWithZero</code></p>",
        "id": 542939500,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759496015
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Concerning the remark about \"non fields\". The way to think about this construction is as follows. If you have a valuation <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">v</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span> on a ring <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">R</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00773em;\">R</span></span></span></span>, then it has a support which is a prime ideal <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathfrak{p}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.713em;vertical-align:-0.1891em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathfrak\">p</span></span></span></span>, and the valuation induces a valuation on the residue field <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>Œ∫</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\kappa(\\mathfrak{p})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Œ∫</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathfrak\">p</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> with the <em>same</em> value group. This construction can be reversed, and so any valuation in the sense of <code>ValuativeRel</code> arises from a valuation on a field.</p>",
        "id": 542940208,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759496239
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"439483\">@Andrew Yang</span> 's example, the support is the zero ideal, so this valuation should really arise from a valuation on the fraction field of the ring.</p>",
        "id": 542940793,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759496413
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"243562\">@Adam Topaz</span> I'm not sure what you're referring to. You seem to be agreeing with Andrew's observation.</p>",
        "id": 542941647,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759496651
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I‚Äôm saying that I don‚Äôt think his example satisfies <code>IsDiscrete</code></p>",
        "id": 542943612,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759497235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, Adam is correct that I overlooked the definition of <code>IsDiscrete</code> and that the current def seems fine to me now.</p>",
        "id": 542943756,
        "sender_full_name": "Andrew Yang",
        "timestamp": 1759497281
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>aha, I also overlooked it because it doesn't show the types in the docs <span aria-label=\"upside down\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f643\" role=\"img\" title=\"upside down\">:upside_down:</span></p>",
        "id": 542947103,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1759498251
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah the notation in the docs can be confusing. It will take some time to get used to the fact that the relation on the ring is denoted <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>‚â§</mo><mi>v</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\le_v</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.786em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mrel\">‚â§</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">v</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and that the value group is the one with a usual order.</p>",
        "id": 542955627,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Topaz",
        "timestamp": 1759500723
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Should we have <code>IsDiscrete =&gt; not DenselyOrdered</code>?</p>",
        "id": 542957846,
        "sender_full_name": "Yakov Pechersky",
        "timestamp": 1759501396
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Just to add an argument from authority: I was reviewing a Habilitation thesis a few weeks ago, on the topic of general valued fields, and I noted two points:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Robinson's (<em>Complete theories</em>, 1956) quantifier elimination theorem for algebraically closed valued fields involves precisely <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ValuativeRel#doc\">docs#ValuativeRel</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/ozAGUxjTkTthUVA5ZgPnpNlU/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/ozAGUxjTkTthUVA5ZgPnpNlU/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1994x1160\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/ozAGUxjTkTthUVA5ZgPnpNlU/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><ul>\n<li>The definition given by the applicant for a discrete valuation field was the existence of a largest element of value <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">&lt;1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.5782em;vertical-align:-0.0391em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">&lt;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n</ul>",
